From 194f7d2c34276d5aa65863bc0b7905def482719c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 02:54:00 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: test nested compact-with-atomic composition
 (do-no-harm)

Adds a torture test for a compact struct whose field is itself a compact
struct containing an atomic. The inner atomic isolation grows Inner to
128 bytes / align 64, and that alignment makes the OUTER compact sort
place Inner first (offset 0), so the small trailing char funnels into the
tail: sizeof(Outer) == 192, versus 256 for the non-compact outer layout
where the char forces the 64-aligned Inner out to offset 64. Confirms the
isolation composes through nesting and the outer reorder still satisfies
do-no-harm. Surfaced while adversarially stress-testing weird field
combinations; no code change needed -- behavior was already correct.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 ...pact-nested-compact-atomic-composition.cpp | 25 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-compact-atomic-composition.cpp

diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-compact-atomic-composition.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-compact-atomic-composition.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..61c769efe
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-compact-atomic-composition.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@
+// Hard/weird scenario: a compact struct whose field is ITSELF a compact struct
+// that contains an atomic. The inner atomic isolation (Inner -> 128B/align64)
+// composes through the outer compact reorder: because Inner now has alignment
+// 64, the outer compact sort places it FIRST (offset 0), funneling the small
+// `char a` into the tail. The result (192) is smaller than the non-compact
+// outer layout (256), where `a` forces the 64-aligned Inner to offset 64. So
+// nesting an isolated atomic still satisfies do-no-harm at the outer level.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct Inner { char x; _Atomic int ctr; int y; };
+compact struct Outer { char a; Inner in; double d; };
+Outer o;
+
+// Inner is isolated to its own cache line: ctr@0, y pushed to 64, sizeof 128.
+static_assert(sizeof(Inner) == 128, "inner atomic isolated");
+// Outer compact sorts the align-64 Inner first, then the double, then the char.
+static_assert(sizeof(Outer) == 192, "outer reorder keeps it tight (vs 256 unsorted)");
+static_assert(alignof(Outer) == 64, "outer inherits the cache-line alignment");
+
+// CHECK:      struct Outer
+// CHECK-NEXT: 0 |{{.*}}struct Inner in
+// CHECK:      128 |{{.*}}double d
+// CHECK-NEXT: 136 |{{.*}}char a
+// CHECK:      sizeof=192, align=64
